# Login System Implementation Plan

This plan details the implementation of a modern login screen backed by a local SQL Server.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> 1. **Tech Stack**: Since no specific language was requested, I propose using **Node.js with Express** for the backend (to connect to your database) and **HTML/Vanilla CSS/JavaScript** for the frontend to offer full control over a premium design. Are you comfortable with this stack?
> 2. **Project Location**: You currently do not have an active workspace. I will create this project at `C:\Users\RPA_COMERCIAL\.gemini\antigravity\scratch\login_system`. You can open this folder in your IDE later.
> 3. **SQL Server Connection Details**: To connect to your local SQL Server, I will need:
>    - Authentication mode: Are you using Windows Authentication or SQL Server Authentication (username/password)?
>    - Existing Database name, or should I write a script to create a new database?

## Proposed Changes

### Database Setup
A SQL script to create a `Users` table storing `Username`, `PasswordHash`, and `Email`.

#### [NEW] database/schema.sql

### Backend Services
A simple Express app that runs locally, connects to the SQL Server via the `mssql` driver, and provides the necessary API endpoints.

#### [NEW] backend/package.json
#### [NEW] backend/server.js
#### [NEW] backend/db.js
#### [NEW] backend/routes/auth.js

### Frontend Interfaces
Premium, animated, and responsive HTML interfaces.

#### [NEW] frontend/index.html (Login)
#### [NEW] frontend/register.html
#### [NEW] frontend/reset.html
#### [NEW] frontend/styles.css
#### [NEW] frontend/app.js

## Verification Plan

### Automated/Manual Tests
- Ensure `npm start` runs the backend successfully.
- Verify that inserting a new user via the UI correctly hashes the password and writes to the SQL Server.
- Verify that attempting to login with valid/invalid credentials responds correctly.
